This is part of the Heritage Trees at Changi Walking Trail, tree no 8.
A strangling fig starts life in the canopy of its host tree. It then extends its aerial roots downwards which progressively surround the hostâ€™s trunk,
which cannot grow and eventually dies. The fig also shades the host by extending its canopy above that of the host tree.
Ficus stricta is a rare lowland rainforest species. Its figs ripen to a purplish red and attract many feeding birds.
